01/05/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Workers across the country will mark International Labour Day on Sunday (May 1st) with demonstrations in Athens and Thessaloniki to protest the government's austerity measures.
Sea and railway transport will be disrupted by a 24-hour strike.
Greeks are unhappy with cuts in wages, pensions and benefits, as well as with tax rises.
(eKathimerini, ANA-MPA, The Voice of Russia - 01/05/11)
